PREHEAT oven to 400 degrees F. COMBINE creamed spinach and cream cheese in medium bowl. Combine pasta, salsa, beef, tomato sauce and chili powder in large bowl. Spoon 1/2 of pasta mixture into 13x9-inch baking pan; top with spinach mixture. Top with remaining pasta; cover. BAKE for 30 minutes; uncover. Sprinkle with cheese; bake for additional 5 minutes.